ch.epfl.alpano.gui

Class PanoramaParametersBean

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.epfl.alpano.gui.PanoramaParametersBean

  • public final class PanoramaParametersBean
extends java.lang.Object
    This class is used to update all the values whenever the user changes them. If the values are wrong (out of bounds) there are put back in the bounds so the program can calculate them correctly. This is possible because each value entered by the user are being watch.
    Author:
    Martin Cibils (261746), Jeremy Mion (261178)

    • Constructor Detail

      • PanoramaParametersBean

        public PanoramaParametersBean(PanoramaUserParameters myPan)
        This constructor initialize a map and a PanoramaUserParamater.

        Each attributes of the PanoramaUserParameter in argument are being observed, put in the map and synchronized with the PanoramaUserParameter whenever the values of the map changes.

        Parameters:
        myPan - The PanoramaUserParamater used to initialize.
